==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|bycġan||obtain by paying a price|lang=ang}}, which is cognate with Gothic {{term|𐌱𐌿𐌲𐌾𐌰𐌽|tr=bugjan|lang=got|sc=Goth}}. Both are ultimately from {{proto|Indo-European|bheug(h)|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/baɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/baI/}}, {{enPR|bī}}
* {{audio|en-us-buy.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪ}}
* Homophones: [[bi]], [[by]], [[bye]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|buys|buying|bought}}

# {{transitive}} To [[obtain]] (something) in [[exchange]] for money or goods
# {{context|transitive|informal}} to [[accept]] as true; to [[believe]]
#: ''I don't '''buy''' that idea.''

====Synonyms====
* (''obtain (something) in exchange for money''): [[purchase]]<!--, [[acquire]], [[shop]]-->
* (''accept as true''): [[accept]], [[believe]], [[swallow]] (''informal''), [[take on]]

====Antonyms====
* (''obtain (something) in exchange for money''): [[sell]], [[vend]]
* (''accept as true''): [[disbelieve]], [[reject]], [[pitch]]

